The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 March is 40,583 (4,697.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 March, there were 368 new confirmed cases (42.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 February, there were 669 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 45% (301 fewer cases).
